2005-06-26 13:39:47 GMT	Richard Kettlewell <rjk@greenend.org.uk>	patch-3

    Summary:
      use curl library rather than executable
    Revision:
      lj2news--mainline--0--patch-3

    If you are likely to re-run aclocal then you will need the libcurl
    autoconf macros on its search path.
    
    * ljrss2news: ljrssexpand now takes a URL
    * ljrssexpand.c: use libcurl to download URL directly instead of
      expecting a local filename.  We run the download in a thread and pipe
      it back into the parser.
    * prepare: use -I option to aclocal not --acdir, so we still see the
      standard archive.

    modified files:
     ChangeLog.d/lj2news--mainline--0 Makefile.am README
     configure.ac ljrss2news ljrssexpand.c prepare


